<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Spartium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="635">Spartium capense</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
, and therefore homotypic with it. Campbell-Young &amp; al. (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="635">Taxon</emphasis>
48: 833. 1999) successfully proposed 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="635">S. capensefor</emphasis>
conservation with a conserved type because all original elements for the name belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="Thunb." authorityName="Thunb." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Rafnia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angulata">
